Primary Data Collection Tools:
• Structured questionnaire with 45 items (validated through pilot study with 30 respondents)
• 7-point Likert scales for attitude measurement (reliability coefficient α > 0.7)
• Ranking exercises for preference ordering
• Demographic profiling (age, income, education, occupation)
• Online survey platform (Google Forms/SurveyMonkey) + offline paper-based surveys

Secondary Data Sources:
• SIAM (Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers) reports
• Government publications (FAME-II scheme data, NITI Aayog reports)
• Industry databases (J.D. Power automotive studies, Frost & Sullivan reports)
